4 Relating to the Emergency Management Agency; to amend
5 Section 31-9-4, Code of Alabama 1975, to authorize the
6 Emergency Management Agency to purchase promotional and
7 educational materials from the funds appropriated to its use;
8 and to delete duplicative language and make nonsubstantive,
9 technical revisions to update the existing code language to
10 current style.
11 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
12 Section 1. Section 31-9-4, Code of Alabama 1975, is
13 amended to read as follows:
14 "§31-9-4
15 (a) There is hereby created within the executive branch
16 of the state government a department of emergency management,
17 hereinafter called the "Emergency Management Agency," with a
18 Director of Emergency Management, hereinafter called the
19 "director," who shall be the head thereof. The director shall
20 be appointed by the Governor. The director shall devote his or
21 her entire time to the duties of the office of director shall
22 be a full-time position. The director shall not hold another
23 office under the government of the United States or any other
24 state, or of this state, or any political subdivision thereof,
25 during his or her incumbency in suchtenure in the office, and
26 shall not hold any position of trust or profit, or engage in
27 any occupation or business the conduct of which shallthat
28 would interfere or be inconsistent with the duties of Director
