32 (b)(1) The director may employ, subject to the
33 provisions of the Merit System ActArticle 1, Chapter 26, Title
34 36, such technical, clerical, stenographic, and otherall
35 necessary personnel and may make such expendituresexpend
36 within the appropriation therefor, or from other funds made
37 available to him or her for purposes of emergency management,
38 as may bethe funds necessary to carry out the purposes of this
39 article; provided, that the state shall not pay the
40 compensation, if any, of block wardens, fire guards, first aid
41 specialists, auxiliary firemen, auxiliary policemen, and
42 similar emergency management personnel, nor shall it pay the
43 compensation of personnel employed by or for a local
44 organization for emergency management.
45 (2) The director's authority pursuant to this
46 subsection includes the use of appropriated funds to purchase
47 items that are reasonably necessary to promote the functions
48 assigned to the Emergency Management Agency by this article,
49 including materials to educate the public on emergency
50 preparedness.
51 (c) The director and other personnel of the Emergency
52 Management Agency shall be provided with appropriate office
53 space, furniture, equipment, supplies, stationery, and
54 printing in the same manner as provided for personnel of other
55 state agencies.
56 (d) The director, subject to the direction and control
