(d) The director, subject to the direction and control
SB8 Enrolled
57 of the Governor, shall be the executive head of the Emergency
58 Management Agency and shall be responsible to the Governor for
59 carrying out the program for emergency management of this
60 state. The director shall coordinate the activities of all
61 organizations of emergency management within the state, and
62 shall maintain liaison with and; cooperate with major
63 commanders of the armed forces within the state, the Alabama
64 State Law Enforcement Agency, the State Military Department,
65 and with emergency management agencies and organizations of
66 other states and of the federal government,; and shall have
67 such additional authority, duties, and responsibilities
68 authorized by this article as may be prescribed by the
69 Governor.
70 (e) The director shall also hold the position of
71 Assistant Director of Homeland Security for Emergency
72 Preparedness and Response."
73 Section 2. This act shall become effective on October
74 1, 2026.
